  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Premium Twin Rooms</strong> are approx. 22-25m² and sleep up to three people. These rooms have a bath with showerhead, balcony and mountain views. </p>
<p><strong>Premium Family Rooms</strong> are approx. 25m² and sleep up to four people (two adults maximum). Two of the beds are bunkbeds and the room has a bath with showerhead, balcony and mountain views. </p>
<p><strong>Deluxe Twin Rooms</strong> are approx. 22m² and sleep up to two people. These rooms have a shower, tea &amp; coffee making facilities, safe and minibar, and balcony with views of the mountains. </p>
<p><strong>Deluxe Family Rooms</strong> are approx. 30m² and sleep up to five people. These rooms have a shower, tea &amp; coffee making facilities, minibar, and balcony with views of the mountains. These rooms are available on request, please call to book.</p>
<p><strong>Standard Twin Rooms</strong> <strong>for sole use</strong> are approx. 22m². These rooms have a bath with showerhead. </p>
<p>Interconnecting Premium Twin and Deluxe Twin Rooms are available on request, please call to book. </p>
<p><em>Please note that some rooms have been renovated, however this is not the case for all rooms and cannot be guaranteed.</em></p>
<p><strong>All rooms have:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
<li>Rooms are simply decorated, but spacious and comfortable.</li>
</ul>]]></roomsDescription>
